BsTool 9.29
COMMAND:	BsTool cmd [parameters]
PURPOSE:
This program operates backup server (bu) in various ways.
Possible commands are:
-tx         [BU server] source destination : transfers file to   bu
-txc        [BU server] source destination : -tx with data compression
-txg        group source destination       : -tx to group members
-rx         [BU server] source destination : receives  file from bu
-move        BU server  source destination : transfer dbfile to  bu
-cat        file                           : displays  file from bu
-ls         filemask                     : bu directory
-rm         filemask                     : delete file(s)
-mv         source destination           : rename file
-crc        filemask(s)                  : file crc calculation
-crcg       group file                   : file crc in multiple BUs
-exec       'script, {}-parm' filemask(s): exec (like find -exec)
-pexec      package filemask 'script'    : exec for modules in package
-gexec      group namemask 'script'      : exec for members in server group
-pextr      package module file          : extract module from package
-piolst     package modulemask           : lists I/O-module addr from package
-connlst    package modulemask#connmask  : lists module connections
-cmiolst    package modulemask [param]   : lists CMIO addr from package
-pmodinfo   package modulemask           : module info: interval, size, etc
-pgen       package file module_files    : generate appl server package
-cpio       [-i xd-root ] [-o xd-file(s)]: cpio dnafiles
-cpio       -l                           : list cpio archive contents
-cp         source destination           : copy dnafile
-cpd        source destination           : copy dnafiles to directory
-cpdir      source destination [-v]      : copy files recursively
-typechk    typename [pro] [typefile]    : print type information
-lgmbr      group                        : list group members
-cmd        passwd server command        : sends command to applserver
- normal  cmds: start, stop, reset
-cnf        passwd server cmd [package]  : sends conf cmd to applserver
- online  cmds: add, del, swap, updval,
accept, reclaim, modules, changed,
connect_err, activate
-db         dbname command parameters    : BU server database tools
following commands are valid
- put     file               : put module into database
- get     module file        : get module from database
- del     module             : delete module from database
- moddel  file               : delete module from database
- list    modulemask         : list db modules
- list    _DB_MODE_          : list db mode (16/32bit)
- pack                       : pack db
- chk                        : check db
- pdiff  modulemask packages : compare modules with package
- exec   modulemask 'script' : exec script for db modules
- crc    modulemask          : CRC-check db modules
- move    dnafile            : transfer filepackage to db
- erase                      : erase/create db
- append  dnafile            : append filepackage to db
- lz      dnafile            : compress db to lz-file
- unlz    dnafile            : append lz-file to db
- extract dnafile            : transform db to filepackage
- usrextr dnafile            :   only configured modules
- sysextr dnafile            :   only system modules
-err        level  device                : diagnostics control
-rd         sector length                : read  disk sectors (#)
-wr         passwd sector length         : write disk sectors (#)
-f          passwd bu                    : format filesystem (#)
-ff         passwd bu                    : format (full) filesystem (#)
-ffc        passwd bu                    : format (full/compressed) (#)
-F          passwd bu master/slave       : format disk (#)
-errlog     server (lid/hw-addr) [cont]
[mask <mask>]            : display RS log messages
-log        count  (0 repetitively)      : display bu log messages
-partition  passwd bu primary/secondary  : select active partition (#)
-backup     passwd bu                    : backup  primary partition (#)
-restore    passwd bu                    : restore primary partition (#)
-mastercopy passwd bu 2 x master/slave   : make mastercopy (#)
-mastercmp         bu                    : compare master and slave (#)
-backupcmp         bu                    : compare with backup (#)
-check             bu                    : check filesystem (#)
NOTE:
Commands which description contain '(#)' mark don't work
with BU-NT.
Use single quotes around file mask to prevent
expansion of '*' or '**' in command line.
Configuration responses can be read with -log. If
communicator is active consult online-log.
Bu name '-' refers to the default bu (connected to RS-line).
Bu boot program on ROM supports only limited command set.
Full set requires appropriate bu code file on drive.
Some shells do not require 's (eg. MSDOS shell on WINNT)
